**Secretary Role.** Any Circle may appoint someone as the Circle's "Secretary". The selected Secretary fills a "Secretary Role" in the Circle, with a Purpose of "Stabilize the Circle's constitutionally-required records and meetings".

The Secretary:

- is accountable for scheduling regular Tactical Meetings and Governance Meetings for the Circle;
- captures and publishes the outputs of those meetings, as well as Governance decisions made asynchronously;
- maintains the Circle's official governance records (Roles, Policies, Strategies) and holds a Domain over the Circle's governance records;
- interprets the Constitution and the Circle's Governance upon request;
- may strike Governance that violates this Constitution from the Circle's records.

A Circle may add Accountabilities or Domains to this Role, but may not amend or remove the Purpose of the Role, nor any Accountabilities or Domains placed on it by this Constitution.
